From: Oleksandr Natalenko <oleksandr@natalenko.name>
Subject: [pf-curated-6.1] ksm: add pmadv_ksm syscall + KSM mm-side hooks

Re-cut from natalenko's pf-kernel branch ksm-6.1 (tip dd595aa539b)
as a single bulk diff, restricted to the files this overlay's curation
kept on the 6.1 LTS slot. Source: codeberg.org/pf-kernel/linux.

Wires up a new pmadv_ksm syscall (a per-process variant of MADV_MERGEABLE
that doesn't require the target process to opt in via prctl). Touches
arch/*/syscalls/syscall*.tbl across all architectures plus the MM-side
hooks in include/linux/ksm.h.
---
